item.title: Need help with this compile error
item.dc:creator: @RandQm RandQm
item.description:
@RandQm wrote:

steelrends:

Mind telling me what it means?.. I’m new to coding

If you want to create a new object, let’s say you want to put a chair in the world and the id of the chair is 526.
Then you have to declare it in your server files obviously.

So then you should have to put: createglobalobject(526);
But the server doesn’t know where to put that chair so you have to add some more things like X coords, Y coords Hight level ect…

You can find this back if you search for “void createglobalobject”

So if you want to add some object, then you search for “createglobalobject”
and you will see some lines like this
createglobalobject(2545, 5652, 5212, 10, 0);

you add the object you want to add under it in the same form

hope this helped you

item.title: Need help with this compile error
item.dc:creator: @RandQm RandQm
item.description:
@RandQm wrote:

createGlobalObject(); ^ required: int,int,int,int,int found: no arguments

What don’t you get?..

If you want to make an object then you obviously can’t put () you have to define where the object has to be and which object ect…
If you don’t know what you have to put, search for another “createglobalobject” line and see how it’s done there

I also don’t suggest using a cfg file for that, though if you really want to, there is a tutorial in the tutorials section
